OL,3,CMum describes 'nightmare' of losing
OL,4,Ctwins as Wales maternity care 'lags
OL,5,Cbehind'
OL,7,FA woman has recounted the "nightmare"
OL,8,Fof losing her twin boys as leading
OL,9,Fbaby loss charities have described
OL,10,Ffailings in maternity care as a
OL,11,F"systemic" problem in Wales.
OL,13,FMum-of-three Ruth Mason, from Merthyr
OL,14,FTydfil, gave birth to identical twins
OL,15,Fin August 2018.
OL,17,FGeorge and Henry, who would have
OL,18,Fturned six this year, died in the
OL,19,Fwomb. Ruth said this was as a result
OL,20,Fof failings in care by Cwm Taf
OL,21,FMorgannwg University Health Board.
