OL,7,F"In the absence of evidence to the
OL,8,Fcontrary, we believe that these issues
OL,9,Fare as relevant in Wales as the rest
OL,10,Fof the UK, and the Welsh Government
OL,11,Fshould do everything in its power to
OL,12,Ftackle these issues and save babies'
OL,13,Flives."
OL,15,FIt comes after the UK health secretary
OL,16,Faccepted calls for a national strategy
OL,17,Fto improve maternity services in
OL,18,FEngland after a into birth trauma
OL,19,Ffound poor-quality care is "all too
OL,20,Ffrequently tolerated as normal".
